The paper deals with the analysis of the classic game Mastermind, which involves guessing a secret code with a limited number of attempts. The paper focuses on the case where the number of colors is large, which suggests that it may fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) or computational complexity (cs.CC). The analysis of the game also involves game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as the paper discusses optimal strategies for playing the game. Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) as it analyzes the amount of information gained from each guess.
